button.description:
## Description
Bouton d'action principal du Design System, disponible en 4 variantes (`primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `danger`) et 3 tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`), rendu obligatoirement via un élément `<button>` natif.

## Spec
- **Border-radius** : `8px` uniforme sur toutes les variantes et tailles (Figma `cornerRadius: 8.0px`)
- **Typographie** : Inter, font-weight 600 — sm: 14px/17px, md: 16px/19px, lg: 18px/22px (source Figma text nodes)
- **Padding** — sm: `4px 16px`, md: `8px 16px`, lg: `8px 24px` (Figma autoLayout padding)
- **Gap icône/texte** — sm: `4px`, md & lg: `8px` (Figma autoLayout gap)
- **États disabled** : fond `#F3F4F6`, texte `#D1D5DB`, curseur `not-allowed` (Figma disabled fills)
- **Focus** : outline `2px solid` décalé de `2px`, couleur `var(--button-focus-ring-color)` via `:focus-visible`

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser `primary` pour l'action dominante d'une zone, une seule fois par vue.
- Toujours spécifier `type="button"`, `type="submit"` ou `type="reset"` explicitement.
- Utiliser l'attribut natif `disabled` pour l'état désactivé.

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas utiliser pour la navigation — préférer un `<a>` quand une URL est attendue.
- Ne pas inventer de variante hors `primary`, `secondary`, `ghost`, `danger`.
- Ne pas surcharger les CSS vars hors de la liste `allowedCssVars`.

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const sizeTokens = {
  sm: {
    paddingX: "var(--button-size-sm-padding-x, 16px)",
    paddingY: "var(--button-size-sm-padding-y, 4px)",
    fontSize: "var(--button-size-sm-font-size, 14px)",
    lineHeight: "var(--button-size-sm-line-height, 1.5)",
    gap: "var(--button-size-sm-gap, 4px)",
    minHeight: "var(--button-size-sm-min-height, 32px)",
    iconSize: "var(--button-size-sm-icon-size, 16px)",
  },
  md: {
    paddingX: "var(--button-size-md-padding-x, 16px)",
    paddingY: "var(--button-size-md-padding-y, 8px)",
    fontSize: "var(--button-size-md-font-size, 14px)",
    lineHeight: "var(--button-size-md-line-height, 1.5)",
    gap: "var(--button-size-md-gap, 8px)",
    minHeight: "var(--button-size-md-min-height, 40px)",
    iconSize: "var(--button-size-md-icon-size, 20px)",
  },
  lg: {
    paddingX: "var(--button-size-lg-padding-x, 24px)",
    paddingY: "var(--button-size-lg-padding-y, 8px)",
    fontSize: "var(--button-size-lg-font-size, 16px)",
    lineHeight: "var(--button-size-lg-line-height, 1.5)",
    gap: "var(--button-size-lg-gap, 8px)",
    minHeight: "var(--button-size-lg-min-height, 48px)",
    iconSize: "var(--button-size-lg-icon-size, 24px)",
  },
};

const variantTokens = {
  primary: {
    bg: "var(--color-action-primary-bg-default, #368e35)",
    bgHover: "var(--color-action-primary-bg-hover, #1D4ED8)",
    bgActive: "var(--color-action-primary-bg-active, #1E40AF)",
    bgDisabled: "var(--color-action-primary-bg-disabled, #F3F4F6)",
    text: "var(--color-action-primary-text-default, #FFFFFF)",
    textDisabled: "var(--color-action-primary-text-disabled, #D1D5DB)",
    border: "var(--color-action-primary-border-default, #368e35)",
    borderHover: "var(--color-action-primary-border-hover, #1D4ED8)",
    borderDisabled: "var(--color-action-primary-border-disabled, #F3F4F6)",
  },
  secondary: {
    bg: "var(--color-action-secondary-bg-default, #FFFFFF)",
    bgHover: "var(--color-action-secondary-bg-hover, #F9FAFB)",
    bgActive: "var(--color-action-secondary-bg-active, #F3F4F6)",
    bgDisabled: "var(--color-action-secondary-bg-disabled, #F9FAFB)",
    text: "var(--color-action-secondary-text-default, #374151)",
    textDisabled: "var(--color-action-secondary-text-disabled, #D1D5DB)",
    border: "var(--color-action-secondary-border-default, #D1D5DB)",
    borderHover: "var(--color-action-secondary-border-hover, #9CA3AF)",
    borderDisabled: "var(--color-action-secondary-border-disabled, #E5E7EB)",
  },
  ghost: {
    bg: "var(--color-action-ghost-bg-default, transparent)",
    bgHover: "var(--color-action-ghost-bg-hover, #F3F4F6)",
    bgActive: "var(--color-action-ghost-bg-active, #E5E7EB)",
    bgDisabled: "var(--color-action-ghost-bg-disabled, transparent)",
    text: "var(--color-action-ghost-text-default, #374151)",
    textDisabled: "var(--color-action-ghost-text-disabled, #D1D5DB)",
    border: "var(--color-action-ghost-border-default, transparent)",
    borderHover: "var(--color-action-ghost-border-hover, transparent)",
    borderDisabled: "var(--color-action-ghost-border-disabled, transparent)",
  },
  danger: {
    bg: "var(--color-action-danger-bg-default, #DC2626)",
    bgHover: "var(--color-action-danger-bg-hover, #B91C1C)",
    bgActive: "var(--color-action-danger-bg-active, #991B1B)",
    bgDisabled: "var(--color-action-danger-bg-disabled, #F3F4F6)",
    text: "var(--color-action-danger-text-default, #FFFFFF)",
    textDisabled: "var(--color-action-danger-text-disabled, #D1D5DB)",
    border: "var(--color-action-danger-border-default, #DC2626)",
    borderHover: "var(--color-action-danger-border-hover, #B91C1C)",
    borderDisabled: "var(--color-action-danger-border-disabled, #F3F4F6)",
  },
};

function Button({ children, variant = "primary", size = "md", disabled = false, onClick, type = "button", icon }) {
  const [hovered, setHovered] = React.useState(false);
  const [pressed, setPressed] = React.useState(false);

  const s = sizeTokens[size];
  const v = variantTokens[variant];

  const bg = disabled ? v.bgDisabled : pressed ? v.bgActive : hovered ? v.bgHover : v.bg;
  const borderColor = disabled ? v.borderDisabled : hovered ? v.borderHover : v.border;
  const color = disabled ? v.textDisabled : v.text;

  return (
    <button
      type={type}
      disabled={disabled}
      onClick={onClick}
      onMouseEnter={() => setHovered(true)}
      onMouseLeave={() => { setHovered(false); setPressed(false); }}
      onMouseDown={() => setPressed(true)}
      onMouseUp={() => setPressed(false)}
      style={{
        display: "inline-flex",
        alignItems: "center",
        justifyContent: "center",
        gap: s.gap,
        paddingInline: s.paddingX,
        paddingBlock: s.paddingY,
        minHeight: s.minHeight,
        fontSize: s.fontSize,
        lineHeight: s.lineHeight,
        fontFamily: "var(--button-font-family, Inter, sans-serif)",
        fontWeight: "var(--button-font-weight, 600)",
        borderRadius: "var(--button-radius, 8px)",
        borderWidth: "var(--button-border-width, 1px)",
        borderStyle: "solid",
        borderColor,
        background: bg,
        color,
        cursor: disabled ? "not-allowed" : "pointer",
        transition: "var(--button-transition, all 150ms ease-in-out)",
        outline: "none",
        boxSizing: "border-box",
      }}
    >
      {icon && (
        <span style={{ width: s.iconSize, height: s.iconSize, display: "inline-flex", alignItems: "center", justifyContent: "center", flexShrink: 0 }}>
          {icon}
        </span>
      )}
      {children}
    </button>
  );
}

const IconPlus = ({ size }) => (
  <svg width={size} height={size} viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" strokeWidth="2" strokeLinecap="round">
    <line x1="8" y1="3" x2="8" y2="13" /><line x1="3" y1="8" x2="13" y2="8" />
  </svg>
);

const variants = ["primary", "secondary", "ghost", "danger"];
const sizes = ["sm", "md", "lg"];

render(
  <div style={{ fontFamily: "Inter, sans-serif", padding: "24px", background: "#f8fafc" }}>
    {/* Matrix: variant × size, enabled */}
    <p style={{ fontSize: "11px", fontWeight: 600, color: "#6B7280", textTransform: "uppercase", letterSpacing: "0.05em", marginBottom: "16px" }}>
      Variants × Sizes — Enabled
    </p>
    <div className="overflow-x-auto">
      <table style={{ borderCollapse: "separate", borderSpacing: "8px", marginBottom: "24px" }}>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style={{ width: "80px" }} />
            {sizes.map(size => (
              <th key={size} style={{ fontSize: "11px", color: "#6B7280", fontWeight: 600, textAlign: "center", paddingBottom: "8px" }}>{size}</th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {variants.map(variant => (
            <tr key={variant}>
              <td style={{ fontSize: "11px", color: "#6B7280", fontWeight: 600, paddingRight: "8px", verticalAlign: "middle" }}>{variant}</td>
              {sizes.map(size => (
                <td key={size} style={{ textAlign: "center", verticalAlign: "middle" }}>
                  <Button variant={variant} size={size}>Button</Button>
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    {/* Matrix: variant × size, disabled */}
    <p style={{ fontSize: "11px", fontWeight: 600, color: "#6B7280", textTransform: "uppercase", letterSpacing: "0.05em", marginBottom: "16px" }}>
      Variants × Sizes — Disabled
    </p>
    <div className="overflow-x-auto">
      <table style={{ borderCollapse: "separate", borderSpacing: "8px", marginBottom: "24px" }}>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th style={{ width: "80px" }} />
            {sizes.map(size => (
              <th key={size} style={{ fontSize: "11px", color: "#6B7280", fontWeight: 600, textAlign: "center", paddingBottom: "8px" }}>{size}</th>
            ))}
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {variants.map(variant => (
            <tr key={variant}>
              <td style={{ fontSize: "11px", color: "#6B7280", fontWeight: 600, paddingRight: "8px", verticalAlign: "middle" }}>{variant}</td>
              {sizes.map(size => (
                <td key={size} style={{ textAlign: "center", verticalAlign: "middle" }}>
                  <Button variant={variant} size={size} disabled>Button</Button>
                </td>
              ))}
            </tr>
          ))}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    {/* With icon */}
    <p style={{ fontSize: "11px", fontWeight: 600, color: "#6B7280", textTransform: "uppercase", letterSpacing: "0.05em", marginBottom: "16px" }}>
      With Icon slot
    </p>
    <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      {variants.map(variant => (
        <Button key={variant} variant={variant} size="md" icon={<IconPlus size="20" />}>
          {variant.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + variant.slice(1)}
        </Button>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
);
```

input.description:
## Description
Champ de saisie texte (`<input>`) supportant trois tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`) et quatre états (`default`, `focus`, `error`, `disabled`). Les tokens de couleur, espacement et typographie sont appliqués via variables CSS.

## Spec
- La spec Figma n'est pas disponible (`figma.available === false`) — les valeurs visuelles sont issues exclusivement des tokens du contrat MCP.
- Tailles : `sm` (min-height 32px, font 14px), `md` (min-height 40px, font 16px), `lg` (min-height 48px, font 18px).
- Border : `1px solid` avec rayon `8px`; couleur varie selon l'état (`default` → `#E5E7EB`, `focus` → `#3B82F6`, `error` → `#EF4444`, `disabled` → `#F3F4F6`).
- Background : `#FFFFFF` par défaut, `#F3F4F6` en état `disabled`.
- Texte : `#111827` par défaut, `#9CA3AF` pour le placeholder, `#D1D5DB` en état `disabled`.
- Padding horizontal et vertical sont définis par taille via les tokens `--input-size-{sm|md|lg}-padding-{x|y}`.

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Associer un `<label>` explicite à chaque champ via `htmlFor` / `id`.
- Afficher un message d'erreur textuel visible en complément de la bordure rouge.
- Utiliser uniquement les tailles `sm`, `md`, `lg` prévues par le contrat.
- Conserver les attributs natifs `disabled`, `value`, `onChange`, `placeholder`.

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas remplacer le composant par un `<textarea>` ou `<select>`.
- Ne pas inventer un état non déclaré (ex. `success`, `warning`, `readonly`).
- Ne pas utiliser le `placeholder` comme substitut au `<label>`.
- Ne pas appliquer de variables CSS hors de la liste `allowedCssVars`.

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const sizeTokens = {
  sm: {
    paddingX: "var(--input-size-sm-padding-x)",
    paddingY: "var(--input-size-sm-padding-y)",
    fontSize: "var(--input-size-sm-font-size)",
    minHeight: "var(--input-size-sm-min-height)",
  },
  md: {
    paddingX: "var(--input-size-md-padding-x)",
    paddingY: "var(--input-size-md-padding-y)",
    fontSize: "var(--input-size-md-font-size)",
    minHeight: "var(--input-size-md-min-height)",
  },
  lg: {
    paddingX: "var(--input-size-lg-padding-x)",
    paddingY: "var(--input-size-lg-padding-y)",
    fontSize: "var(--input-size-lg-font-size)",
    minHeight: "var(--input-size-lg-min-height)",
  },
};

const stateTokens = {
  default:  { border: "var(--input-border-default)",  bg: "var(--input-bg-default)",   color: "var(--input-text-default)",   outline: "none" },
  focus:    { border: "var(--input-border-focus)",    bg: "var(--input-bg-default)",   color: "var(--input-text-default)",   outline: "2px solid var(--input-border-focus)" },
  error:    { border: "var(--input-border-error)",    bg: "var(--input-bg-default)",   color: "var(--input-text-default)",   outline: "none" },
  disabled: { border: "var(--input-border-disabled)", bg: "var(--input-bg-disabled)",  color: "var(--input-text-disabled)",  outline: "none" },
};

const stateLabels = {
  default:  "Default",
  focus:    "Focus",
  error:    "Error",
  disabled: "Disabled",
};

function DSInput({ size = "md", state = "default", placeholder = "Placeholder", value, onChange, ...rest }) {
  const s = sizeTokens[size];
  const t = stateTokens[state];
  return (
    <input
      {...rest}
      disabled={state === "disabled"}
      placeholder={placeholder}
      value={value}
      onChange={onChange}
      style={{
        display: "block",
        width: "100%",
        minHeight: s.minHeight,
        paddingInline: s.paddingX,
        paddingBlock: s.paddingY,
        fontSize: s.fontSize,
        fontFamily: "inherit",
        lineHeight: "1.5",
        color: t.color,
        background: t.bg,
        border: `var(--input-border-width, 1px) solid ${t.border}`,
        borderRadius: "var(--input-radius)",
        outline: t.outline,
        outlineOffset: state === "focus" ? "2px" : undefined,
        boxSizing: "border-box",
        cursor: state === "disabled" ? "not-allowed" : "text",
        opacity: state === "disabled" ? "0.6" : "1",
      }}
    />
  );
}

function PreviewCell({ size, state }) {
  const [val, setVal] = React.useState(state === "default" ? "" : state === "focus" ? "Valeur saisie" : state === "error" ? "Valeur invalide" : "Désactivé");
  return (
    <div className="flex flex-col gap-1">
      <label style={{ fontSize: "11px", color: "#6B7280", fontFamily: "inherit" }}>
        {size.toUpperCase()} / {stateLabels[state]}
      </label>
      <DSInput
        id={`input-${size}-${state}`}
        size={size}
        state={state}
        placeholder="Placeholder"
        value={val}
        onChange={(e) => setVal(e.target.value)}
      />
      {state === "error" && (
        <span style={{ fontSize: "12px", color: "var(--color-danger-500)", fontFamily: "inherit" }}>
          Ce champ est invalide.
        </span>
      )}
    </div>
  );
}

render(
  <div className="p-6 bg-gray-50 min-h-screen">
    <h2 className="text-lg font-semibold mb-6 text-gray-800">Input — Matrice size × state</h2>
    <div className="grid grid-cols-4 gap-x-6 gap-y-8">
      {["sm", "md", "lg"].map((size) =>
        ["default", "focus", "error", "disabled"].map((state) => (
          <PreviewCell key={`${size}-${state}`} size={size} state={state} />
        ))
      )}
    </div>
  </div>
);
```

card.description:
## Description
Conteneur de contenu structuré (`<article>`) avec padding, rayon et élévation pilotables par tokens. Décliné en 3 variantes (`default`, `elevated`, `outline`) et 3 tailles (`sm`, `md`, `lg`).

## Spec
- **Dimensions Figma** : composant 400 × 540 px, `cornerRadius: 8px`, layout colonne (`flex-direction: column`)
- **Background** : fill solid `#FFFFFF` → token `--card-bg`
- **Ombre** : `0px 0px 6px 0px rgba(0,0,0,0.25)` (Figma) ; token `--card-shadow` (default) / `--shadow-200` (elevated)
- **Bordure** : absente sur les variantes Default/Elevated Figma ; présente via `--card-border` (`#E5E7EB`) sur la variante `outline`
- **Radius** : `8px` Figma → token `--card-radius` (resolvedValue `12px` selon contract)
- **Padding par taille** : `sm` → `--card-padding-sm` (16px) · `md` → `--card-padding-md` (24px) · `lg` → `--card-padding-lg` (32px)

## Do & Don't
✅ **Do**
- Utiliser `<article>` ou `<section>` selon le contexte sémantique du contenu
- Regrouper un contenu homogène et hiérarchiquement cohérent dans la card
- Piloter l'élévation uniquement via les tokens de shadow déclarés

❌ **Don't**
- Ne pas utiliser la card comme bouton ou élément interactif cliquable
- Ne pas imbriquer plus de deux niveaux de cards
- Ne pas utiliser de variables CSS hors de `allowedCssVars`

## Code interactif (Live Editor)

```jsx
const paddingMap = {
  sm: "var(--card-padding-sm)",
  md: "var(--card-padding-md)",
  lg: "var(--card-padding-lg)",
};

const shadowMap = {
  default: "var(--card-shadow)",
  elevated: "var(--shadow-200)",
  outline: "none",
};

const borderMap = {
  default: "none",
  elevated: "none",
  outline: "1px solid var(--card-border)",
};

function Card({ size = "md", variant = "default", children }) {
  return (
    <article
      style={{
        display: "flex",
        flexDirection: "column",
        gap: "12px",
        width: "280px",
        background: "var(--card-bg)",
        borderRadius: "var(--card-radius)",
        padding: paddingMap[size],
        boxShadow: shadowMap[variant],
        border: borderMap[variant],
      }}
    >
      {children}
    </article>
  );
}

function CardContent({ title, body }) {
  return (
    <>
      <strong style={{ fontSize: "1rem", lineHeight: "1.4" }}>{title}</strong>
      <p style={{ fontSize: "0.875rem", lineHeight: "1.5", margin: 0 }}>{body}</p>
    </>
  );
}

const variants = ["default", "elevated", "outline"];
const sizes = ["sm", "md", "lg"];

render(
  <div className="p-8 bg-gray-100 min-h-screen">
    {variants.map((variant) => (
      <div key={variant} className="mb-10">
        <p className="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-500 mb-4">
          variant = {variant}
        </p>
        <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-6 items-start">
          {sizes.map((size) => (
            <Card key={size} size={size} variant={variant}>
              <CardContent
                title={`Card · ${variant} · ${size}`}
                body="Conteneur de contenu regroupant des informations homogènes avec padding et élévation pilotés par tokens."
              />
            </Card>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>
);
```
